Pre-Game Insights: Milwaukee Bucks and Utah Jazz face off in a cross-conference game on November 8, 2024.
Milwaukee Bucks finished last season with a 49-33 record, including a strong 31-11 home record.
Utah Jazz finished last season with a 31-51 record, struggling on the road with a 10-31 record.
Milwaukee averaged 14.5 points off turnovers, 13.1 second-chance points, and 32.5 bench points last season.
Utah averaged 115.7 points per game, 53.3 points in the paint, 14.9 points off turnovers, and 13.9 on fast breaks last season.
Key players like Giannis Antetokounmpo and Lauri Markkanen are listed as day-to-day with injuries.
